          "End of Course",
          "Authors removed multiple irrelevant logs and group the remaining ones according to a taxonomy of Authentication, Overall Site, Profile and Social Interactions.\n\nThese are later grouped into components.\n\nFrom here, the authors look at the behavior of students across different components - aggregate them into learning activities and look at the learning sequence to identify abnormal times on task - outliers.\n\n\nThe authors look at course and activity to identify how to deal wioth these outliers.\n\nAuthors compare 6 distinct forms of outlier treatment.",
          "Multiple Linear Regression",
          "None Specified",
          "PG\n{R-Squared: 0.951 - MedianMAD - Local}\n\nUG\n{R-Squared: 0.829 - IQRMed-Local}",
          "Authors propose a distinct way of identifyng outliers when it comes to time spent on tasks. Authors compare 6 forms of outlier definition and treatment:\n\nMeanSTD: Replace outliers with mean\n\nMedianMAD: uses Median to fill\n\nIQRMed: Uses Median on IQR\n\nIQRWinsor: Winsorizes\n\nZ-Score: Removes all outside regular z-score range\n\nTrimmedMean: Uses a trimmed mean instad of the full mean.\n\nOther than that, authors also consider different possible absolute of thresholds for activities.\n\n",
          " -  No model assessment strategy\n\n - Small sample size\n\n - Only uses Multiple Linear Regression"
        ],
