    {
      "id": "1ab4750c-f3ba-80b5-920f-d5e42e4b9361",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Time-on-task is a popular construct in the learning analytics literature. However, pre-processing details are often unmentioned which affects reproducibility of steps done. Authors propose a method for time on task estimation that takes into account differences in activities. Real-world experiments show that method outperforms current state-of-the-art. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "1ab4750c-f3ba-80b5-920f-d5e42e4b9361",
        "parent": {
